 FLAME 1. v. To speak incessantly and/or rabidly on some relatively
uninteresting subject or with a patently ridiculous attitude. 2. To post an
email message intended to insult and provoke. FLAME ON: v. To continue to
flame. see RAVE, BURBLE. The punning reference to Marvel comics' Human Torch
has been lost as recent usage completes the circle: "Flame on" now usually
means "beginning of flame".